sbml2modelica.preprocessing

Class SyntaxPreprocessingManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • sbml2modelica.preprocessing.PreprocessingManager
      • sbml2modelica.preprocessing.SyntaxPreprocessingManager

  • public class SyntaxPreprocessingManager
extends PreprocessingManager
    A SyntaxPreprocessingManager pre-processes a SBML Model in order to handle those identifiers that could conflict with some Modelica keyword.
    It recomputes all the identifiers of the elements of a SBML Model adding them a prefix. The same operation, with a different prefix, is applied to the arguments of the functions.
    Note that a SyntaxPreprocessingManager also adds the prefixes to the variables in every formula appearing in the SBML Model.
    Author:
    Maggioli Filippo

    • Method Detail

      • addPrefixes

        private static org.sbml.jsbml.ASTNode addPrefixes(org.sbml.jsbml.ASTNode formula,
                                                  java.lang.String prefix)
        This method add the given prefix to every variable in the given ASTNode, that is to every node with type AST_NAME.
        Further, it adds the prefix ELEMENT_ID_PREFIX to every user defined function, that is to any node with type AST_FUNCTION.
        Parameters:
        formula - The ASTNode whose the prefixes must be added.
        prefix - The prefix to add to the variables.
        Returns:
        The given ASTNode, with the prefixes.
